dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model

Class OpenReferences

  • java.lang.Object
    • dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.OpenReferences

  • public class OpenReferences
extends java.lang.Object
    This class stores open references of entities (references that don't have a target entity yet). These references are tried to be resolved after merging two models - see TresosDBModelMerge.startMerge(dreisoft.tresos.datamodel2.data.node.classmodel.IClassEntity, dreisoft.tresos.datamodel2.data.node.classmodel.IClassEntity, dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.IEntity.MergeFlags, org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor, dreisoft.tresos.lib2.util.OperationStatus)
    Since:
    2009.a

      • getOpenReferences

        public OpenReferences.OpenEntityReferences getOpenReferences(IEntity entity)
        Returns the OpenReferences.OpenEntityReferences object of the given entity. This object holds all open references of the entity.

        This can be used in conjunction with addOpenReferences(IEntity, OpenEntityReferences) to transfer the open references of one model to another one (e.g. during merge).
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity for which the open references shall be returned
        Returns:
        The OpenReferences.OpenEntityReferences object of the entity or null
        Since:
        10

      • addOpenReferences

        public void addOpenReferences(IEntity entity,
                              OpenReferences.OpenEntityReferences references)
        Adds the given OpenReferences.OpenEntityReferences to the open references of the given entity.

        This can be used in conjunction with getOpenReferences(IEntity) to transfer the open references of one model to another one (e.g. during merge).
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity that holds the open references
        references - The OpenReferences.OpenEntityReferences that shall be added (may be null)
        Since:
        10

      • load

        public void load()
        Loads the open references stored in the associated TresosDB from disc. This must only be called, if the associated TresosDB is file based!

        If this already holds any open references, these are discarded and replaced by the loaded ones.
        Since:
        10

      • save

        public void save()
        Stores the open references to the associated TresosDB. This must only be called, if the associated TresosDB is file based!

        If the associated TresosDB already contained any open references, these are discarded first.
        Since:
        10
